	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.80]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Actually you raise some excellent questions. The thing to keep in mind though, is that even though pets con blue to you they're still strong. The straight pets, (ie. Water, earth, air and fire) usually are only a couple levels lower than you and for quite a while are prolly gonna be pretty even to the mobs you'll be fighting for exp.<br><br>And actually I think you misunderstood. The range usually was within about 5 levels (with exceptions at early level) However, aside from the first few levels, pets would never con anything higher than blue and would sometimes con lightblue. What this patch did is made it so that while a pet will never be equal level to you (pre 60) your pets will still summon the highest in the range possible.<br><br>let me give an example. And forgive me if this is incorrect, working off the data of others.<br><br>For the level 34 spell cast at that level, your pet would be somewhere in the range of 25 to 29. 25 and 26 being light blue and 27 28 and 29 being blue. Now as you leveled up to 39 only the 28 and the 29 pets would con blue. The other three would be light blue and the 27 one is just one step up from being solid green.<br><br>What the patch changed was to arrange it so every time you cast the lvl 34 pet spell it ALWAYS summons the lvl 29 pet, meaning you get the best out of the deal.<br><br>So if anything this patch was a Very Good Thing[tm]<br><br>In regard to our soloing abilities, mages are extremely effective soloers, up to about level 52, when grouping becomes safer and as fast or faster. That depends on how good you are at soloing though. <br><br>There ARE methods of soloing over 52 but these get dangerous and require you to REALLY be on your toes. If ya got the game for it it's doable tho.<br><br>We are on par with necros with soloing in most regards. Superior in some, deficient in others. The class balancing regarding soloing is pretty close though for the classes it applies to. It's just the methods that are different.<br><br>But yeah, mages can quite easily cut it on their own if need be. We are a very good solo class.<br><br><br><br>Faelawen Starfyre, the Mad Mage of Povar<br><br>Faelawen auctions: WTB crown of elemental mastery for 1000pp<br>Faelawen auctions: ....<br>Faelawen auctions: ....<br>Faelawen auctions: dammit...<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
