	   <tr><td colspan=2>In my experience, I was actually the one breaking mez on the mob, though the enchanter thought it was my pet.&nbsp;&nbsp;I had already cast elemental maelstrom on the mob (our dot).  THEN the enchanter mezzed it.  He couldn't figure out why my pet kept attacking.  Well, it's because my dot was breaking the mez, NOT my pet.<br><br>Since they made the change to not allow pets to break mez, this is the only circumstance in which I have had a problem.  Otherwise, I get the message &quot;I beg forgiveness, master, I am unable to wake (mob)&quot; or some similar message.<br><br>I don't often hunt with enchanters, so I'm accustomed to being the team member who takes care of single adds.  I usually sick my pet on it, cast my dot and go back to nuking the main mob.  I learned it's a good idea to warn an enchanter before fighting that magicians now can cast a DOT.  Of course the enchanters have to learn that when fighting in a group which includes a magician, it's not usually necessary to mez a single add.  Now 2 or more adds, that's a different story.<br>&nbsp;<br>Merry meet, merry part, and merry meet again.<br><br>Yanari, Witch of Felwithe</td></tr>
