	   <tr><td colspan=2>NO TO MY KNOWLEDGE THERE HAVE BEEN NO RECENT SPELL CHANGES TO THE... *finds his capslock key...*<br><br>*Ahem* sorry. no recent changes to the effects of mage spells, or an increase to their gradiation. However as you gain levels there will be a *slight* increase in the rate at which they gain power. But there is a cap where they stop increasing in effectiveness. <br><br>If you want to see the exact data on spells, download a program called EqCaster. It reads your sp.dat file in your eq directory to give you a list of every spell in the game. updates automatically whenever they add new spells too, because it gets the data straight from your computer. It's the place people get all the spell info you see posted here.<br><br>As to the type of pet to use in a group situation, it depends. Got a rogue in your group? Go with air, stuns give em a little extra BS time. Your pet gonna be doing all the tanking? Fighting mobs that bolt at low life? Go with earth and DS it. Fighting mobs where you're likely to have your pet offtanking adds that poison? .... ok that one won't happen too often, but hey, water works there. If your pet is backing up another tank (which is likely in most situations) almost any of the pets will work. It all depends on specifics. <br><br>You can, will, and need to be able to answer that kind of question for yourself or yer not gonna get far as a mage. Learn exactly what your pets can do. Parse it. Live for the data. Then eventually you'll customize your own stratigies for solo, group and raid situations.... However if you're looking for a quick and easy answer, either should work fine. There is a situational difference, but it's a bit like fine tuning a car. It's gonna run either way, just gonna work better if you know exactly what everything does.<br><br><br>I swear one of these days I need to just write a comprehensive mage guide.<br><br><br>-The Mad Mage<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Fri Feb 14 11:04:44 2003</em><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
